{
  "stem": "16473.3",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 390.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the first book I read was by Bettelheim, he was one of my professors at the U of C.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I did read that book.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And from then, I slowly ventured into reading.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But I didn't associate myself as being a survivor until I started reading books about child survivors.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And among them, they included children who were in hiding.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And even though I wasn't in hiding with strangers, as my cousins were.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They lived in France and they were sent to Switzerland and they lived with strangers.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I wasn't hiding in that sense, but I was in hiding with the papers.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So I felt and I still feel reluctant to call myself a survivor, except that I did survive.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And I wouldn't have if I hadn't had the papers.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "My grandparents who stayed in Vienna did not survive, they died on the cattle cars.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I have other relatives that did not survive because they were directly in the work camps or on their way-- I mean, to the concentration camps or on their way to the concentration camps.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "However, I feel very strongly about being a Jew.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And if anybody says anything about a Jew, I will be the first one to say I am a Jew, even though I'm a convert.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "I feel very important to say that I am a Jew.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "When my children got older, I enrolled them in a Hungarian school so they could practice Hungarian.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And I have very strong feelings about Hungary.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "They're good feelings.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And my husband is Hungarian, and so I wanted them to have that exposure, only to find out that the people there were quite Anti-Semitism.",
      "word_count": 25
    }
  ],
